[[File:Shoufukuji01.jpg|thumb|Rōmon]]

{{Nihongo|'''Shōfuku-ji'''|聖福寺}} is a [[Rinzai]] temple in [[Hakata-ku, Fukuoka|Hakata]], [[Fukuoka, Fukuoka|Fukuoka]], [[Japan]].  Its honorary ''[[Buddhist temples in Japan#sangō|sangō]]'' prefix is {{nihongo|''Ankokuzan''|安国山}}.  It was founded by [[Eisai]] with support from [[Minamoto no Yoritomo]], and construction was completed in 1195, making it the oldest [[Zen]] temple in Japan.

